<div class="tldr-box">
  <h3>TL;DR, Mailmodo for Indian marketers</h3>
  <p>The Indian-built AMP email platform. Interactive forms and polls inside the email body, AI subject lines, WhatsApp omni-channel, Shopify and Razorpay integration. INR pricing, UPI accepted, GST invoice. Strongest pick for Indian D2C and SaaS marketing teams running email-led funnels.</p>
  <a href="https://www.mailmodo.com" class="cta-button">Try Mailmodo</a>
</div>

<p>Most Indian D2C brands run on three channels: email, WhatsApp, and Instagram. Of these, email is the most under-utilised because the templates feel old and the click-through funnels feel like work for the customer. AMP email solves this by letting the customer act inside the email itself. Mailmodo is the Indian-built ESP that took the AMP-first bet and now serves a large chunk of Indian D2C and SaaS marketing teams.</p>

<h2>What makes Mailmodo different</h2>

<h3>AMP email natively supported</h3>
<p>Forms, polls, surveys, product carousels, calendar embeds, RSVPs, all rendered inside Gmail (which is the bulk of Indian inboxes). Customer fills, scrolls, clicks, no need to load a landing page. Open-to-conversion rates step-change.</p>

<h3>AI-driven optimisation</h3>
<p>Subject-line generation, copy variations for A/B, send-time optimisation per recipient, smart segmentation. Material gains on open rate and CTR for teams that previously sent generic blasts.</p>

<h3>WhatsApp omni-channel</h3>
<p>Run the same campaign across email and WhatsApp with channel-appropriate copy. For Indian D2C funnels where WhatsApp typically closes what email opens, this matches behaviour.</p>

<h3>Indian integrations</h3>
<p>Shopify (D2C), Razorpay (payments), Webengage, Segment, HubSpot. The Indian D2C and SaaS stack works out of the box.</p>

<h2>What Mailmodo costs Indian users</h2>

<p>Tiered by contacts and email volume. Approximate INR ranges:</p>

